[38;2;255;255;255mâº[39m Based on my analysis using LLDB with tmux, I have identified the root
  cause of the crash in the [38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy[39m program:

  [1mRoot Cause Analysis[22m

  [1mWhere it crashes:[22m
  - File: [38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy.c[39m at line 26
  - Function: [38;2;177;185;249madd_score(Student *s, float score)[39m
  - Specific line: [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores] = score;[39m

  [1mWhy it crashes:[22m
  The program crashes with an [1mEXC_BAD_ACCESS (code=1, address=0x0)[22m error,
  which is a null pointer dereference.

  [1mThe Problem:[22m
  1. The [38;2;177;185;249mStudent[39m structure has a [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m field that should point to an array
   of floats to store student scores
  2. When examining the student structure, I found that [38;2;177;185;249mscores = [39m
  0x0000000000000000 (NULL pointer)
  3. The [38;2;177;185;249mcreate_student[39m function apparently creates a Student but fails to
  allocate memory for the [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m array
  4. When [38;2;177;185;249madd_score[39m is called, it tries to write to [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[0][39m, but since
   [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m is NULL, this causes a segmentation fault

  [1mVariables at crash time:[22m
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms[39m (Student pointer): [38;2;177;185;249m0x000000011de05580[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->name[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m"Alice"[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->age[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m20[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m0x0000000000000000[39m (NULL - this is the problem)
  - [38;2;177;185;249ms->num_scores[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m0[39m (valid)
  - [38;2;177;185;249mscore[39m: [38;2;177;185;249m95.5[39m (valid parameter)

  [1mCall Stack:[22m
  1. [38;2;177;185;249mmain()[39m at line 56: calls [38;2;177;185;249madd_score(alice, 95.5)[39m
  2. [38;2;177;185;249madd_score()[39m at line 26: attempts to dereference NULL pointer [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[39m

  The bug is in the student creation process where the [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m array is not
  properly allocated, leaving it as a NULL pointer. When the program tries
  to add the first score, it crashes immediately.
